article.headline: Southern Cal 92, Oregon 73
article.story:
LOS ANGELES --  Briana Gilbreath narrowly missed a triple-double, with 18 points, 11 assists and nine rebounds, leading USC to a 92-73 win over Oregon Thursday night.

Gilbreath also blocked five shots in the win, which was the fifth in a row for the Trojans (10-6, 5-1 Pac-12).

Cassie Harberts added 17 points, Christina Marinacci had 14 points and 10 rebounds and Alexyz Vaioletama had 12 points for USC, which trailed 12-4 early but roared back to lead 49-36 at halftime.

Liz Brenner led the Ducks (10-9, 2-5) with 16 points. Jasmin Holliday added 14 points and Jordan Loera scored 13 for Oregon.
